The paper deals with pattern matching, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and is studied in various subfields. The use of wildcards and the streaming model suggest that the paper may belong to the data structures (cs.DS) or data mining (cs.DM) categories. The use of randomized algorithms and space complexity suggest that the paper may also belong to the computational complexity (cs.CC) or information theory (cs.IT) categories. Finally, the use of machine learning techniques for pattern matching suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category.
